.TH NETCHECK 1 "June 2026" "version 2.2.0" "Network Intelligence Engine"
.SH NAME
netcheck \- cross-platform network diagnostics, connectivity checks, and path analysis
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B netcheck
\fISUBCOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR]
.br
.B netcheck
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIinput_file\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B netcheck
is a zero-dependency, cross-platform, production-grade network diagnostic engine.
It resolves DNS, tests TCP connectivity, validates HTTP responses, inspects SSL/TLS certificates,
pings hosts, lists active interfaces, traces network routes, performs port scans,
and looks up domain/IP registration details.
.P
Supports JSON/CSV/XML structured output, watch/loop mode, concurrent bulk checks via thread pools,
CIDR and IP range expansion, and an integrated Model Context Protocol (MCP) server for AI assistants.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B tcp \fIhost\fR \fIport\fR
Check TCP port reachability. Supports port lists (80,443) and ranges (8000-8010).
Respects IP ranges (192.168.1.1-50) and CIDR subnets (10.0.0.0/24).
.TP
.B dns \fIhost\fR
Resolve DNS A/AAAA records for a hostname. Reports IP addresses, CNAME aliases, and reverse DNS.
.TP
.B http \fIurl\fR
Inspect HTTP/HTTPS response: status code, redirect chain, content size, and latency.
Supports custom methods (\fB--method\fR), headers (\fB-H\fR), and Basic Authentication (\fB--auth\fR).
.TP
.B ssl \fIhost\fR [\fIport\fR]
Inspect the SSL/TLS certificate of a host. Reports subject, issuer, validity dates, days until expiry,
TLS version, cipher suite, and SHA-256 fingerprint. Default port is 443.
.TP
.B ping \fIhost\fR
Ping a host using ICMP and display RTT statistics (min/avg/max) and packet loss.
.TP
.B interfaces
List local network interfaces, their IPv4/IPv6 addresses, status (UP/DOWN), default gateway, and public IP.
.TP
.B ports
List local listening TCP ports, identifying PIDs/processes and mapping to active Docker container names where applicable.
.TP
.B traceroute \fIhost\fR
Trace the network path (hop-by-hop) to the destination. Uses raw ICMP sockets if permissions allow,
otherwise falls back to the system
.BR traceroute (8)
/
.BR tracepath (8)
(Linux/macOS) or
.BR tracert (1)
(Windows).
.TP
.B scan \fIhost\fR
Perform a concurrent TCP port scan on the target host. Defaults to a curated set of ~44 common ports.
Use \fB--ports\fR to specify custom ports or ranges.
.TP
.B whois \fItarget\fR
Look up registrar and registration details for a domain or IP using RDAP (HTTP JSON API).
Falls back to a legacy WHOIS TCP socket query on port 43 if RDAP fails.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -t ", " --timeout " \fIsec\fR"
Connection timeout per check in seconds (default: 5). Override with \fBNETCHECK_TIMEOUT\fR env var.
.TP
.BR -j ", " --jobs " \fInum\fR"
Maximum concurrent threads for batch TCP checks (default: 10). Override with \fBNETCHECK_MAX_WORKERS\fR env var.
.TP
.BR -f ", " --format " \fIfmt\fR"
Output format: \fBtext\fR (default), \fBjson\fR, \fBcsv\fR, \fBxml\fR.
.TP
.BR -V ", " --verbose
Verbose output: shows extended details such as response headers, SANs, and raw WHOIS data.
.TP
.BR --no-color
Disable ANSI color codes in output. Also honoured via \fBNO_COLOR\fR and \fBNETCHECK_NO_COLOR\fR env vars.
.TP
.BR -w ", " --watch
Enable watch/loop mode: repeats the check at a regular interval until Ctrl+C.
.TP
.BR -i ", " --interval " \fIsec\fR"
Refresh interval for watch mode in seconds (default: 2.0).
.TP
.BR --retry " \fIcount\fR"
Number of connection attempts per target (default: 1).
.TP
.BR --retry-delay " \fIsec\fR"
Delay between retry attempts in seconds (default: 1.0).
.SH HTTP SUBCOMMAND OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -X ", " --method " \fIMETHOD\fR"
HTTP request method: GET (default), HEAD, POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH.
.TP
.BR -H ", " --header " \fI'Key: Value'\fR"
Add a custom HTTP request header. Repeatable.
.TP
.BR --auth " \fIuser:pass\fR"
HTTP Basic Authentication credentials.
.SH TRACEROUTE SUBCOMMAND OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -m ", " --max-hops " \fInum\fR"
Maximum number of hops to trace (default: 30).
.SH SCAN SUBCOMMAND OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -p ", " --ports " \fIspec\fR"
Comma-separated port list or range (e.g. 80,443 or 80-1024). Defaults to ~44 common ports.
.SH LEGACY OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -q ", " --quick " \fIhost\fR \fIport\fR"
Quick TCP connection test (equivalent to: netcheck tcp).
.TP
.BR -d ", " --dns " \fIhost\fR"
DNS lookup (equivalent to: netcheck dns).
.TP
.BR -p ", " --ping " \fIhost\fR"
Ping host (equivalent to: netcheck ping).
.TP
.BR -s ", " --status " \fIurl\fR"
HTTP status check (equivalent to: netcheck http).
.TP
.BR --cert " \fIhost\fR"
SSL certificate check (equivalent to: netcheck ssl).
.TP
.BR --my-ip ", " -ip
List network interfaces (equivalent to: netcheck interfaces).
.TP
.BR --mcp
Start the integrated Model Context Protocol (MCP) JSON-RPC stdio server.
.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
.TP
.B NETCHECK_TIMEOUT
Overrides the default connection timeout (float, seconds).
.TP
.B NETCHECK_MAX_WORKERS
Overrides the default parallel thread pool size (integer).
.TP
.B NO_COLOR
If set to any value, disables ANSI color output (per https://no-color.org/).
.TP
.B NETCHECK_NO_COLOR
Alternative to NO_COLOR for disabling color output.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Quick TCP check:
.B netcheck tcp google.com 443
.TP
DNS lookup with JSON output:
.B netcheck dns github.com -f json
.TP
HTTP check with custom method and header:
.B netcheck http https://api.example.com -X POST -H "Authorization: Bearer token"
.TP
SSL certificate with full cipher details:
.B netcheck ssl google.com -V
.TP
Traceroute with limited hops:
.B netcheck traceroute 8.8.8.8 -m 15
.TP
Port scan with custom range:
.B netcheck scan 192.168.1.1 --ports 1-1024 --jobs 100
.TP
WHOIS lookup for a domain:
.B netcheck whois google.com
.TP
Watch TCP connection every 2 seconds:
.B netcheck tcp 8.8.8.8 443 --watch --interval 2
.TP
Show active network interfaces:
.B netcheck interfaces
.TP
Show active listening ports and services:
.B netcheck ports
.TP
Batch check from file:
.B netcheck -t 10 -j 20 hosts.txt
.TP
Start MCP Server:
.B netcheck --mcp
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR traceroute (8),
.BR ping (8),
.BR nmap (1),
.BR curl (1)
